HI. Me and my team are using the pathplanner software in order to make paths and autos. We have separated the paths for each piece into different paths and then stitch them up in a auto, however, we are having trouble running a command that runs alongside the paths. Right now for a piece our structure includes a parallel command group inside the main sequential group, a path and another parallel command group with the command to collect and some other commnads, and then finally we shoot using the autoaiming while moving command (works in teleop) outside of the big parallel command group. Because of this, we always stop to shoot inside of just driving and shooting at the time. Does anyone have any suggestion that would make it work with the parallel group and the shoot command? Thank you for reading!

This is really hard to follow. Can you share your code, or at least your PathPlanner files, or some screenshots?

Are you using event markers and named commands to run the shoot command while the path is running? If youâ€™re putting the command in your auto between paths, thatâ€™s when it will run. To run a command during a path, you probably want an event marker.
